{
  "texts": [
    "Empathy is referred to as the capacity for comprehending and reciprocating the feelings of another.",
    "Sympathy, on the other hand, is the ability to share comparable feelings with another individual.",
    "People with ASD may not be able to empathize or sympathize with others (Cheng et al. 2002).",
    "When someone is harmed, they may express gladness, or they may show no emotion at all.",
    "As a result of their inability to respond correctly to others' emotions, autistic people may appear emotionless."
  ]
}